Interface TableMapView<K,V>

    public interface TableMapView<K,V>
extends Map<K,V>
    A view of data in a table as a Map. The values will themselves be maps or other tables.

    • Method Detail

      • getViewForKey

        V getViewForKey(K key)
        Returns a view of the value for a given key. If the value is itself a map or nested table and the key is not present, this will return an empty such map or table, not null. The returned view is modifiable. Changes to the returned view are visible via other operations on the map and vice versa.

        Note that if this map is a view that does not allow adding elements then the returned view will also not allow adding elements. In such a case this method and get(Object) will not actually behave differently.

        Parameters:
        key - the key
        Returns:
        a modifiable view of the value for the given key, an empty map or table if no such key exists
        See Also:
        get(Object)

      • get

        V get(Object key)
        Returns the value mapped to the given key. Unlike normal maps, if the value is itself a map or nested table and the key is not present, this will return an empty such map or table, not null. The returned view is not fully modifiable. In particular, new elements/mappings cannot be added through the returned view. But deletions are allowed. Deletions on the returned view are visible via other operations on the map. Other changes made via map operations are visible via the returned view.
        Specified by:
        get in interface Map<K,V>
        Parameters:
        key - the key
        Returns:
        a view of the value for the given key
        See Also:
        getViewForKey(Object)

      • remove

        V remove(Object key)
        Removes the value mapped to the given key and returns it. Unlike normal maps, if the value is itself a map or nested table and the key is not present, this will return an empty such map or table, not null.
        Specified by:
        remove in interface Map<K,V>
        Parameters:
        key - the key of the mapping to remove
        Returns:
        the value that was removed, possibly empty if the given key was not present
        See Also:
